&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the manufacturing and production of flight hardware from prototype through low-rate and scaled production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and improve build processes for airframes, avionics, power systems, and integration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop tooling, fixtures, work instructions, and quality checks that enable speed and repeatability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with design engineers to make hardware more manufacturable, reliable, and scalable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive root-cause analysis and corrective actions on build and test issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support integration, environmental testing, and flight operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help stand up production capabilities inside our El Segundo factory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 style=&quot;color: #0000ee;&quot;&gt;What we’re looking for&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years working as a manufacturing, production, or build engineer on real hardware&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience building mechanical, electrical, or aerospace systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong intuition for tolerances, processes, and how things actually get built&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working closely with design engineering teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to move fast, own outcomes, and solve problems on the factory floor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort operating in ambiguous, fast-moving environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
